# ============================================================================
# Inverted .gitignore (whitelist mode)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Everything is ignored by default; only files that are explicitly listed
# below (or in a nested .gitignore inside an un-ignored directory) are
# tracked. This keeps the repo clean of generated / user-local / binary noise
# and requires a conscious decision for any new artefact to enter history.
#
# How to add something new:
#   - At the top level: add a `!name` line here.
#   - Inside backend/frontend/electron/docs: edit that directory's own
#     .gitignore — each subtree manages its own whitelist.
# ============================================================================

# Start by ignoring every file at the root.
*

# Essential root files
!.gitignore
!README.md
!CLAUDE.md
!package.json
!package-lock.json

# Managed directories — each has its own nested .gitignore.
# Un-ignoring the directory here lets git descend into it; the per-directory
# .gitignore then decides which files inside to track.
!backend/
!frontend/
!electron/
!docs/
